&nbsp;
"In different forms, a renewed 'domanda' &nbsp; of politics emerged very clearly, understood as a set of values, ideality, a sense of being together and sharing of design through a bottom-up mechanism that has not always been present," explains Marwa Mahmoud, Head of Political Formation in the National Secretariat of the PD. The idea of the two days of Frascati is to equip the territories of a 'cassetta of tools', tools and skills to be put in the field in the daily management of party life and to greater reason on the occasion of election campaigns. The event is conceived as the start of a path of participation and national formation, which starting from the involvement of girls and boys under 35 from all federations, build a community of activists and activists who during the campaign for Europeans will work together with the thousands of PD militants, using innovative tools.
&nbsp;
"A full immersion in which about 200 girls and boys from all over Italy will confront trainers, experts and political leaders and will test themselves in the organization and management of an electoral campaign in all its aspects," concludes Marwa Mahmoud. The works, which will be closed, will start in the evening today, Friday 12 April and end on Sunday 14 April in the morning.&nbsp;

