AGI -&nbsp; "A perfect combination", says the subtitle of the seminar attended by Elly Schlein and Giuseppe Conte. A claim that could not sound more ironic, in one of the moments of higher tension in the relations between the Democratic Party and the 5 Star Movement. The appointment was conceived long before the explosion of the case Bari and the 'strap' between Conte and the leader dem. The goal was to cement the axis between dem and five stars from environmental themes: "Water and Sun, a perfect combination", is the full title of the initiative held in the House of Montecitorio groups opened by the two responsible for the climate and the ecological transition of the two parties, Annalisa Corrado for the dems and Gianni Pietro Girotto for the M5s. And instead. Elly Schlein arrives in Montecitorio before Count and attends most of the works. He sits in his place even when the seminary is ending and Count has not yet appeared in the classroom. The speakers seem to take time, the secretary wants to wait for the M5s homologue. And Conte returns courtesy by greeting her and thanking her from the stage.
&nbsp;
The tone is courteous, the two leaders exchange smiles and, for a short time, lay together on the stage. It is perceived, however, a certain coldness left of days of angry polemics. The first step towards the resumption of dialogue is done, although it is still early to talk about disintegration. In Parliament, especially in the PD front, long and mugly muses remain. On the contrary, the local levels continue to seek as evidenced by the informal encounter between the Tuscan exponents of the Democratic Party and Movement 5 Stars in Montecitorio. A first survey to assess whether there are conditions to present themselves together with the administrative elections in the region and, above all, in Florence. At the top, which took place in a room of the Chamber of Deputies, participate the representatives of the secretariat dem Davide Baruffi and Igor Taruffi, the Cinque Stelle Paola Taverna, the MP M5s Andrea Quartini, the regional secretary of the Pd, Emiliano Fossi, the local body manager of the Pd Toscana, Stefano Bruzzesi. At the end of the meeting, some of the participants speak of "positive climate" among the parties: "A first face-to-face interlocutor who might follow others." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
The name for the dems in Florence remains that of Sara Funaro, is underlined. Only four days ago, Pd and M5s found the agreement in Prato, with the candidate dem Ilaria Bugetti. To this is added what happens in Sardinia, with the composition of the Regional Council by Alessandra Todde. The M5s Governor used the balance sheet to distribute the delegates, with two councillors of weight to the Five Stars (Health and Work), and three to the Pd, to which also the vice-president of the Junta and the presidency of the Regional Council. A 'double standard' between national and local level that seems to respond to the dual challenge that awaits the two parties. That of the Europeans, where we vote with proportionality and preferences, and that of the administrative ones, where it is necessary to join if we want to have some hope of victory.
&nbsp;
The leader dem is expected, first of all, from the first appointment that, except for surprises, will see it in the field in person. The direction called to dissolve the nodes on the table, beginning with those of the leaders, has not yet been convened, but parliamentary sources of the Pd bet that the leader dem will not wait on 28 April, last term to present the lists, but will convoke the party's speaking between 15 and 18 of the month. As for the list heads, the eyes are aimed at Stefano Bonaccini: if the president of Emilia-Romagna will put as a condition for his candidacy that of being lined up on the top of the list North East will jump the scheme of the five female leaders. Bonaccini, in fact, would take the place of Annalisa Corrado in that constituency, with Cecilia Strada leading the list of the North West. In the center, the node concerns Nicola Zingaretti, who competes with Camilla Laureti and Dario Nardella in the role of headmaster, without forgetting Marco Tarquinio, former director of Avvenire on which Schlein decided to aim to strengthen the bond with the Catholic electorate. In the South there should be no problem for Lucia Annunziata and in the Islands the name on which is pointed is that of Pietro Bartolo, the doctor of Lampedusa who appears among the outgoing Euro MPs. In this scheme, the name of Schlein should appear deeper in the lists: between the third and fourth place, depending on the pattern that will be chosen.&nbsp;

